narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Increased knowledge of Chinese politics and societal issues. Significant practice in listening, speaking, reading and writing Chinese.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Very strong course overall, though the textbook could be updated. Many articles in the textbook were written a decade ago.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Absolutely. The course content is very interesting and Professor Su is one of the best instructors Ive had at Yale.
Yes! Su Laoshi is great -- even after a bad time with Chinese at boring Sunday Chinese school growing up, his stories and energy made me love it again.
